# This is a manual patch instruction

There are two separate cases to handle. Apply both independently.

---

## Case 1: A `ContentLinkGroup` or `ContentLink` component is already wrapping a `DefaultStructuredText`

Replace the `ContentLinkXXX` component with a plain element and add the `contentLinkAttrs` helper.

Before:
```astro
<ContentLinkGroup class="text ui-richtext">
    <DefaultStructuredText data={data.text} />
</ContentLinkGroup>
```

After:
```astro
<div class="text ui-richtext" {...contentLinkAttrs({ group: true })}>
    <DefaultStructuredText data={data.text} />
</div>
```

---

## Case 2: A `DefaultStructuredText` is wrapped in a plain element **without** any `ContentLinkXXX` component

Add the `contentLinkAttrs` helper with `{ group: true }` to the existing parent element.

Before:
```astro
<div class="text ui-richtext">
    <DefaultStructuredText data={data.text} />
</div>
```

After:
```astro
<div class="text ui-richtext" {...contentLinkAttrs({ group: true })}>
    <DefaultStructuredText data={data.text} />
</div>
```


